Hey, party people! 

I’m Jesse and I serve as the director of marketing for PhoneBurner.

My background is eclectic at best. 

I come from the stereotypical West Virginian family, with a coal-minder dad and stay-at-home mom. I originally cut my teeth in selling insurance. Found my way into non-profit work. Stumbled into content marketing nearly 10-years ago. Wound up in the publishing industry for a handful of years. For the past several years, I’ve been in B2B SaaS marketing. 

And, for a shameless plug, I co-authored a book called “Read to Lead” that’s releasing in August. It has been endorsed by Seth Godin, Stephen Covey, Michael Hyatt, and several others. Really pumped about getting this into the hands of readers soon. 

I’m excited to join this community, make new friends, learn, and have some fun along the way.

text:
:wave: Hey folks, I’m Nick and I lead growth marketing at Mailgun and Mailjet. We help companies like Lyft, Wikipedia, Cinemark, and Zapier send and deliver emails. We send over 15 billion emails/month which gives us tons of data to analyze and also creates fun scalability problems for our engineers to solve.

My background is in paid search. I wrote an article last year about spending $6 million on Google Ads that hit the front page of Hacker News and changed my life.

I’ve been blogging more on my personal website with a goal to grow my monthly visitors to 10k (halfway there!), so I’m here to learn and pickup tips I can use on my personal site and also apply to my day job as well.

Hey folks :wave:
My name is <https://www.linkedin.com/in/levinschi/|Dan Levinschi> and I’m the VPM at <https://www.tremendous.com/|Tremendous>. It’s a YC-incubated startup in the fintech space. We’re building a rewards & incentives platform (gift cards).
My background — born and raised in <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moldova|Moldova>, spent all of my career in Tech. Started at Google (Poland, Ireland, UK, US), where I spent most of my career, then joined the startup world. I’ve built the marketing functions from scratch at PandaDoc and Fleetsmith, the latter got acquired by Apple last year. And now I’m at Tremendous doing my thing all over again.
Feel free to hit me up if you have any questions. I’m also happy to take part inactive discussions and share my knowledge and experience. Very excited to have joined this community. :star-struck:

text:
<@U01AHL8AGBB> — we’re not necessarily competing, but let me persuade you to give us a try:
• International support
    ◦ Guusto works in US/CA only.
    ◦ Tremendous works internationally in more than 80 countries and our distribution is growing.
• Redemption options
    ◦ Guusto offers merchant gift cards only.
    ◦ Tremendous offers merchant gift cards + bank/ACH transfers + charity contributions.
• Price
    ◦ Guusto costs money if you upgrade from the personal plan.
    ◦ Tremendous is 100% free for any size team, you pay for what you send.
• Support
    ◦ I’m not sure what happens if a recipient cannot redeem a gift card.
    ◦ Tremendous takes care of the support side for recipients, so you don’t have to deal with that. Free of charge.
• Use cases
    ◦ Guusto is built for employee recognition.
    ◦ Tremendous is built for employee recognition, consumer promotions, partner incentives, sales incentives, customers, etc. Just about any use case where a gift card could help.
• Our API is the best in the industry.
